## Overview

This is an R Markdown document. The document generates the following 3 plots:

1. ICS account balances by state and year (stacked bar)
1. Deposits and debits to ICS accounts by state and year (stacked bar)
1. Stacked line plot that show Lake Mead Storage, Water Conservation Account (ICS) Balance, and reservoir protection elevation over time. The plot also shows a line of the anticipated Lake Mead storage volume were the Water Conservation Program not exist (states continued withdraws at their historical allocations).

## Data wrangling strategy

1. Import the reservoir elevation-volume curves
1. Import the water conservation account data for Lake Mead
1. Import historical reservoir storage data
1. Turn annual ICS data into Monthly, Calculate the Lake Mead Elevation without ICS accounts, and turn reservoir, ICS, and protection volumes into dataframe in narrow format for ploting as a stacked line graph.


The plots support the analysis of the work: "Lake Mead Water Conservation Accounts: Examples, Successes, Challenges, and Potential Improvements post 2026."

